# SPA route allow-list.
#
# Adding a top-level 404.html disables Cloudflare Pages' default
# "serve index.html for everything (200)" single-page-app fallback, so any path
# that is neither a static asset nor listed below now returns a real 404 (via
# 404.html). That stops vuln-scanner probes (/.env, /wp-admin/*, /.git/config,
# /xmlrpc.php, ...) from getting a 200 app shell.
#
# Every genuine client route from V1_ROUTE_DEFINITIONS (src/routes.ts) must be
# rewritten back to the app shell with a 200 so deep links / refreshes still
# boot the SPA. "/" is the real index.html asset and needs no rule. Splats cover
# the nested cases (e.g. /g/:id/obs, /overlay/:id/:variant).
#
# Destination is "/" (not "/index.html"): Pages auto-strips "/index" and ".html"
# for pretty URLs, so a rewrite to /index.html is detected as an infinite loop
# and silently ignored. Rewriting to "/" serves the same root index.html.
/create        /   200
/manage/*      /   200
/g/*           /   200
/overlay/*     /   200
